        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-14 13:55:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nYes, the workaround was originally for saturation of logstash - after looking into it post the Daemonset change - it turned out the CPU saturation is only when AAI is on the same node - in this case the secondary workaround is to limit the vCPU to 3 until I fix the root cause.  We will revisit the daemonset when we bring in a file instead of beats plugin to get the logs directly from docker.  For now yes we should revert this because the daemonset is not being used correctly anyways for traffic - I like the labels idea better",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
